creator: Dahar Games
descriptionHtml:
Kite flying is a popular sport in India and Pakistan. There was even a time when men fought brutal battles in the skies with their kites. Meaning of kite battle is kites swerving and swooping in the sky, tangling with each other until the string of one was severed"

In India Vs Pakistan Kite Fly game is for Fun you can do kite fly battle just for fun. Select your country and start flying kite in blue sky. You will be able to learn sport spirit with this kite game. Don’t lose yourself as here you will be playing on behalf of your country name.

How to play and win kite flying adventure game:
1. Select your country
2. Select kite and threads
3. Start flying kite and patch with your opponents
4. When patch is done either give dheel or khech as fast as you can
5. If your speed of tapping is fast then the opponent then you will win
6. Upgrade your kite and reels to give best challenge

We have introduced different Game Mode:

You can select different kite model from Pipa, Wau Bulan, Wau Kucing, Layang, patang, Pião Raia, Treme Treme, Patang, Guda, Nakhlaoo, Pan, Tukal, Muchal, Farfarata, etc. and reels (Manjah) model from Biowow, Winder winding reel, kizh kite reel, emma kite kelvar line, tar, dore, pench, manjoh, kai po che, volantin, cerol etc..

India:
Fighter kites are known as patang in India. In many others, kite flying takes place mainly during specific festivals particularly the spring festival known as Basant, during Makar Sankranti

Pakistan:
Kite flying in Pakistan is social event that happen once in year. Lahore is considered as kite batting in south Asia. In the past, kite battling had a status of sports in Lahore, and those kite flyers were termed as "Khilari" or sportsman. Celebration is going for two days long Bassant or Spring Festival in Pakistan.

We are sure that you love this kite battle game. If you have any suggestion then writes us a mail.

More surprises are coming soon for all kite fly lovers. Stay tune to get update.

NOTE: India Vs Pakistan Kite Fly IS JUST FOR FUN. DON’T TAKE ANYTHING AS A SERIOUS. WE REQUEST BOTH COUNTRIES’ PEOPLE TO ENJOY THIS GAME WITHOUT ANY BAD INTENTION.
